input_str: December 20, 2010 was the first time we saw James Reimer in the Leafs net. Coming in for the inadequate Jonas Gustavsson mid game, the young goalie played well in his first career appearance. A relative unknown to Leafs fans at the time, he would soon take Leafs Nation by storm as the team embarked shortly thereafter on an incredible run that saw the team fall just short of a playoff berth. After years of inconsistent and sometimes downright awful goaltending, Toronto saw a ray of hope,
